What Makes Pepper Spray Effective!<br/><br/>&lt;P&gt;The active ingredient in pepper spray is Oleoresin Capsicum (O.C.), usually referred to as red pepper. Oleoresin Capsicum is a non-lethal, non-toxic, non-flammable solution which ispressurized with C02 in aerosol form.&lt;/P&gt;
<br /><br />&lt;P&gt;If you are wondering which <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5zZWN1cml0eWFuZHNlbGZkZWZlbnNlc3RvcmUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL3BlcHBlci1zcHJheS9waXN0b2wtZ3JpcC1wZXBwZXItc3ByYXktdW5pdC5odG1s" target="_blank">pepper spray</a> is most effective, one must consider two key factors influencing the effectiveness of your pepper spray solution: the percentage of pepper being used and the heat rating of that pepper measured in Scoville Heat Units or (S.H.U.). &lt;/P&gt;
<br /><br />&lt;P&gt;Pepper spray allows you to protect yourself and offers effective self defense and keeps you a safe distance from an assailant. A one second spray at the facial area induces temporary blindness swells the veins in eyes making them to slam close, choking and restricting breathing , coughing, and nausea. Pepper spray use will force your assailant to their knees with results lasting as long as 45 minutes. &lt;/P&gt;

Mini surveillance cameras<br/><br/>&lt;p&gt;Board cameras are mini cameras that feature a digital lens affixed onto a tiny circuit board. <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5zZWN1cml0eWFuZHNlbGZkZWZlbnNlc3RvcmUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL3NlY3VyaXR5LWNhbWVyYXMvbWluaS1jYW1lcmFzLmh0bWw_" target="_blank">Mini security cameras</a> are often only one inch by one inch so they are ideally suited for surveillance camera system applications where discretion is needed.&lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;p&gt; <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5zZWN1cml0eWFuZHNlbGZkZWZlbnNlc3RvcmUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL3NlY3VyaXR5LWNhbWVyYXMvbWluaS1jYW1lcmFzLzYwNy1oaS1yZXMtYm9hcmQtY2FtZXJhLWNvbG9yLTM4MC1saW5lcy5odG1s" target="_blank">Mini surveillance cameras</a> are frequently the camera of choice for covert surveillance camera systemmonitoring. Some board cameras  even use pinhole lenses. On average a pinhole lens is 1/16” diameter. This is the only part of the camera that must be exposed for a picture to be obtained. &lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;p&gt;There are two types of pinhole lenses – flat and conical. Conical lenses require a smaller hole and are often used in <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5zZWN1cml0eWFuZHNlbGZkZWZlbnNlc3RvcmUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2NhbWVyYS1zeXN0ZW1zLmh0bWw_" target="_blank">surveillance camera systems</a> using ceiling tiles. Flat lenses need a larger hole but are better when your security camera system is to be situated in thin material, like clothing. &lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;p&gt;With their smaller hole size the pinhole lens will have a somewhat lower resolution than a board lens. which is usually 1/2 inch in diameter, thereby allowing more light to get in.&lt;/p&gt;

Use Bio Scan Technology for Your Home or Office!<br/><br/>&lt;p&gt;
<br /><a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5zZWN1cml0eWFuZHNlbGZkZWZlbnNlc3RvcmUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2tleS1oaWRlcnMvOTYzLWJpb21ldHJpYy1kZWFkYm9sdC1kb29yLWxvY2stYW50aXF1ZS1icmFzcy5odG1s" target="_blank">Finger print access control</a> 
<br />These units utilize a finger print scanner to recognize individuals and give automated security. It is usually used at mentry points of a building to make sure that only permitted people can enter a building or restricted area. Finger print scanning technology is being utilized to provide security for many items, including homes. For homes (or an office), the embedded scanning software allows the <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5zZWN1cml0eWFuZHNlbGZkZWZlbnNlc3RvcmUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2tleS1oaWRlcnMvOTYyLWJpb21ldHJpYy1kZWFkYm9sdC1kb29yLWxvY2stbmlja2VsLXBsYXRlZC5odG1s" target="_blank">finger print scanner to grant access</a> to those it recognizes and deny access to anyone whose prints do not match any of the prints previously scanned into the door knob database during setup.&lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;p&gt;Finger Print Scanning technology offers a sophisticated degree of security, as fingerprints cannot be faked or loaned to another person to use. Plus, fingerprints are not lost or mislaid. For these reasons, finger scanning is being used for lots of unique security purposes. Biometric scanner development has lead to improvements in fingerprint scanning for access reasons and the implementation of bio scanning for computers, security boxes, plus portable finger print scanners now used by banks or the police. &lt;/p&gt;
